ZH: 他们在生气的时候总是大声争吵。
EN: They always argue loudly when they are angry.

ZH: 她生了一场大病，现在还在康复中。
EN: She had a serious illness and is still recovering.

ZH: 生活中有许多不可预测的事情。
EN: There are many unpredictable things in life.

ZH: 我们必须学会在压力下生存。
EN: We must learn to survive under pressure.

ZH: 在这个行业里要想成功，必须有强烈的生存欲望。
EN: To succeed in this industry, one must have a strong will to survive.

ZH: 他对未来充满了希望和生机。
EN: He is full of hope and vitality for the future.

ZH: 人类必须与自然和谐共生。
EN: Humans must coexist harmoniously with nature.

ZH: 生于忧患，死于安乐。
EN: Born in distress, die in ease.

ZH: 生存环境的恶化对于许多动物都是生死攸关的。
EN: The deterioration of the living environment is a matter of life and death for many animals.

ZH: 这种植物能在恶劣的环境中生长。
EN: This plant can grow in harsh environments.

ZH: 让我们充分利用我们的时间，生活得更充实。
EN: Let's make the most of our time and live a more fulfilling life.

ZH: 生活充满了各种各样的挑战和机遇。
EN: Life is full of various challenges and opportunities.

ZH: 年轻时学习，年老时有所依赖。
EN: Learn while young, rely on when old.

ZH: 漫漫长夜，饥寒交迫。
EN: In the long night, suffering from hunger and cold.

ZH: 生活不止眼前的苟且，还有诗和远方。
EN: Life is not just about the drudgery of the moment, but also about poetry and distance.

ZH: 生于忧患，死于安乐。
EN: Born in suffering, die in peace.

ZH: 只有勇往直前，才能战胜生活的困难。
EN: Only by moving forward courageously can we overcome the difficulties of life.

ZH: 他的生活方式非常健康。
EN: His way of life is very healthy.

ZH: 经历过生死离别的人，更懂得珍惜眼前的幸福。
EN: People who have experienced life and death separation understand the value of present happiness.

ZH: 现在是好好把握住生活的时候了。
EN: Now is the time to seize life.
